#Implement the Linear Regression model
class MultipleLinearReg:
    def fit(self, X, y):
       
        X = np.c_[np.ones(X.shape[0]), X]  
        
        try:
            
            self.w = np.linalg.inv(X.T.dot(X)).dot(X.T).dot(y)
        except np.linalg.LinAlgError:
            print("Matrix is singular and cannot be inverted.")
            self.w = None

    def predict(self, X, show=False, data_label="Data"):
        if self.w is None:
            raise ValueError("Model has not been fitted yet or the matrix was singular.")

       
        X = np.c_[np.ones(X.shape[0]), X]

        
        y_hat = X.dot(self.w)

        
        if show:
            plt.figure()
            plt.scatter(X[:, 1], y_hat, s=8, label=data_label)
            plt.plot(X[:, 1], y_hat, color="#FE0070", label="Regression Line")
            plt.xlabel('X')
            plt.ylabel('y')
            plt.title('Linear Regression Fit')
            plt.legend()
            plt.show()

        return y_hat

#Implement Regression with Gradient Descent
class MultipleLinearRegGD:
    def __init__(self, learning_rate=0.01, n_iterations=315, regularization=0.0):
        self.learning_rate = learning_rate
        self.n_iterations = n_iterations
        self.regularization = regularization 
        self.w = None
        self.scaler = None

    def fit(self, X, y):
       
        
        self.scaler = StandardScaler()
        X = self.scaler.fit_transform(X)

       
        X = np.c_[np.ones(X.shape[0]), X]
        
        
        self.w = np.random.randn(X.shape[1])
        
        m = len(y) 
        
        # Gradient Descent loop
        for _ in range(self.n_iterations):
            
            y_hat = X.dot(self.w)
            
            
            gradient = (1 / m) * X.T.dot(y_hat - y) + (self.regularization / m) * self.w
            
            
            self.w -= self.learning_rate * gradient

    def predict(self, X):
       
        if self.w is None:
            raise ValueError("Model has not been fitted yet.")

       
        X = self.scaler.transform(X)
        X = np.c_[np.ones(X.shape[0]), X]

       
        return X.dot(self.w)

def mean_absolute_error(y_true, y_pred):
    return np.mean(np.abs(y_true - y_pred))

def calculate_accuracy(y_true, y_pred):
    mae = mean_absolute_error(y_true, y_pred)
    mean_y = np.mean(y_true)
    accuracy = 100 - (mae / mean_y * 100)
    return accuracy
